grch37-haploinsufficient-genes-clingen-v.summary: The 'clingen_hi_gene' haploinsufficient gene set comes from ClinGen's Dosage Sensitivity Map and is curated by Daniel MacArthur's lab. The genes used are those that are haplosensitive and not triplosensitive, and are level 3 (the maximum level) dosage sensitive. Original work on this is part of the Cytogenomic Arrays Consortium. Paper at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5008023/

grch37-haploinsufficient-genes-dang-v1.summary: The haploinsufficient gene set comes from Dang et al. (2008): https://www.nature.com/articles/ejhg2008111.
